The Nobel Laureate, Prof. Wole Soyinka; a former senator representing Kaduna Central, Sen Shehu Sani; a former Chairman of the National Human Rights Commission, Prof. Chidi Odinkalu, activist Deji Adeyanju, amongst others are at the Federal High Court in Abuja to support Sahara Reporters publisher, Mr. Omoyele Sowore, who is being prosecuted for organising a nationwide protest tagged #RevolutionNow. See photos:       